gomodel:SYNGO_1481  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: Serotonin2A receptor immunoreactivity was observed in 325 identifiable structures. Of these, 24% were presynaptic axons and varicosities; most of these had morphological features that were characteristic of monoamine axons: thin diameter, lack of myelination, occasional content of dense-cored vesicles, and infrequent formation of synapses in single sections: this was not validated, though.. Experimental description: Four naive adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (Hilltop Laboratory Animals, Scottsdale, PA, USA) were used..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
